quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
42,1,"Ha'. Mim."
42,2,"Ayn. Sin. Qaf."
42,3,"Thus does Allah, the Most Mighty, the Most Wise reveal to you even as (He revealed) to those (Messengers) who preceded you. {1}",footnotes:1:The style of the opening verses by itself shows that in the background there are the misgivings
42,4,"His is all that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth; He is the Most High, the All-Great. {1}",footnotes:1:These introductory sentences are not meant to be said merely in praise of Allah Almighty
42,5,"The heavens may well nigh rend asunder from above {1} while the angels proclaim the praise of their Lord and ask forgiveness for those on earth. {2} Lo, it is Allah, and He alone, Who is Most Forgiving, Most Merciful. {3}",footnotes:1:That is
42,6,"Those who have taken others than Him as their protectors beside Him, {1} it is Allah Who oversees them; you are no guardian over them. {2}",footnotes:1:The word auliya (sing. wali) as used in the text is very comprehensive in meaning. The different beliefs and all sorts of diverse practices with regard to the false deities held and worshiped by the polytheistic people
42,7,"And thus did We reveal this Arabic Qur'an {1} to you that you may warn the people of the Mother of Cities (to wit, Makkah) and those who dwell around it; {2} and warn them of the Day of Gathering {3} concerning which there is no doubt: whereon some will be in Paradise, and some in the Blazing Fire.",footnotes:1:That is
42,8,"If Allah had so willed, He could have made them all a single community. But He admits whomsoever He pleases into His Mercy. As to those given to wrong-doing, they shall have none as protector or helper. {1}",footnotes:1:This theme has three objects in this context:
42,9,"(Are they so foolish that) they have chosen others rather than Allah as their protectors? Yet it is Allah Who is the Protector and Who resurrects the dead and Who has power over everything. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
42,10,"The {1} judgement on whatever you differ rests with Allah. {2} Such is Allah, {3} my Lord; in Him I have put all my trust and to Him I always turn in devotion. {4}",footnotes:1:From here to the end of( verse 12)
